Package: survalis
Type: Package
Title: Interpretable and Causal Machine Learning Methods for Survival Analysis
Version: 0.5.0
Author: Imad El Badisy [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Imad El Badisy <elbadisyimad@gmail.com>
Description: A modular toolkit for interpretable and causal survival machine learning. 
    Includes many built-in learners (e.g., statistical models, tree-based models, deep leanring models) and supports 
    user-defined models that return time-indexed survival 
    probability matrices. Provides model-agnostic interpretability methods such as SHAP, 
    PDP, ALE, surrogate models, feature importance, and counterfactual explanations. 
    Also enables causal survival inference including average treatment effects, RMST, 
    and conditional treatment effects (CATE) with visualization tools. Designed to integrate 
    seamlessly via a unified fit and predict interface.
